data.content:
泉城购电动自行车以旧换新平台
泉城购电动自行车以旧换新平台is an online platform for registering and managing the electric bicycle trade-in subsidy program.

济南市
济南市is the administrative region where the 2025 electric bicycle trade-in subsidy program is implemented.

Government Subsidy
Government Subsidy provides financial support to consumers purchasing new electric bicycles after trading in old ones.<SEP>A financial incentive provided by the government to support the purchase of new electric bicycles.

Recycling Companies
Recycling Companies handle the disposal of old electric bicycles in compliance with program standards and regulations.

Consumer Registration Process
Consumer Registration Process involves signing up on the泉城购电动自行车以旧换新平台platform, submitting old bicycle information, and receiving a subsidy eligibility code.

Electric Bicycles
Electric Bicycles are the focus of the trade-in program aimed at replacing outdated models with new, qualified ones.

Sales Entities
Sales Entities participating in the program facilitate the trade-in of old bicycles and the sale of new qualified models.

2025 Electric Bicycle Trade-In Subsidy Program
The 2025 Electric Bicycle Trade-In Subsidy Program in济南市promotes replacing old electric bicycles with new ones, offering financial incentives.

Subsidy Eligibility Code
Subsidy Eligibility Code is a unique code generated for consumers to access government subsidies during the purchase of new electric bicycles.

District/County Commerce Departments
District/County Commerce Departments are administrative bodies responsible for preliminary review and approval of activity participants before reporting to the city-level Commerce Bureau.

Personal Consumer
The individual entity involved in the purchase or trade-in of electric bicycles, responsible for negotiating vehicle residual values and providing accurate information for subsidies.

Recycling Entity
The organization involved in accepting old vehicles for trade-ins during the subsidy program.

Fiscal Subsidy Fund
A designated funding source allocated by the government for subsidies related to the electric bicycle program.

City-Level Commerce Authority
The regional governing body responsible for overseeing commerce-related activities and approving special pricing circumstances.

Policy Brochure
A detailed guide issued by sales entities to explain subsidy policies, pricing, and consumer rights.

Consumer Complaint Channel
A system set up by authorities to handle and resolve consumer complaints during the subsidy activity period.

Subsidy Conflict Responsibility
The accountability of sales entities in cases of subsidy-related disputes caused by their operational errors.

Subsidy Indicator
A measure or quota limiting the number of subsidy claims a consumer may use during the activity period.

Vehicle Company
A business involved in the manufacturing and sale of electric bicycles and providing additional discounts in combination with government subsidies.

Store Discounts
A supplementary savings program offered by stores participating in the electric bicycle subsidy activity.

Consultation Hotlines
Phone numbers provided for consumer inquiries during the subsidy activity period.

Sales Entity
The organization responsible for selling electric bicycles, issuing invoices, and handling subsidy-related matters.

Return Policy
The rules governing the reimbursement process for refunds during the subsidy program, including exclusion of subsidy funds and payment channel restrictions.

Fraudulent Activities
Illegal practices such as providing false information, fake transactions, cross-region repetitive purchases, hoarding, and subsidy fraud that are subject to legal consequences.
